<h2> How It Started </h2>
<table>
  <tr>
    <th> The Lakers began their franchise when Ben Berger and Morris Chalfen bought the disbanded team Detroit Gems franchise of the National Basketball League (NBL).
         The business partner was Maury Winston and the head coach was  John Kundla. The franchise was given a new name, the "Lakers" in reference to Minnesota's nickname, "The Land of 10,000 Lakes"
         Berger and Chalfen brought in Max Winter  to become the Lakers' new general manager. Winter also took an ownership stake in the team. </th>
    <th>
      <p>John Kundla </p>
      <img src="https://vignette2.wikia.nocookie.net/nba/images/6/6a/John_Kundla.jpeg/revision/latest?cb=20170112105449" alt="past image" style="width:200px ; height:250px "> </th>
  </tr>
</table>
